Researched by See research team Reviewed by Bri Field Assigning Editor Updated 8 22 Great fiber service, if you can get it CenturyLink offers excellent fiber internet, but it’s available only in limited If you can t get fiber, you may be able to get a DSL connection but you ll pay nearly as What we like Unlimited data across all plans Fast fiber connections in select markets No contracts What we dislike Limited fiber availability Much slower DSL internet speeds customer service Our expert assessment Value Great fiber value meets , DSL plans CenturyLink offers two types of plans, depending on your The more common option is DSL , which is relatively slow and offers inconsistent The other option is fiber , which is extremely fast and Generally speaking, the DSL options are not a great The price is reasonable, but the speeds mean you’re likely to get more for your money elsewhere (this is true for many DSL providers). The fiber plans are a much better value—they offer much more speed for the money than CenturyLink’s DSL plans and are competitive with other providers’ fiber In fact, CenturyLink s Mbps plan costs a little more than half of the national benchmark for similar plans (1). We highly recommend CenturyLink fiber if you have it Show details Performance Performance is excellent for areas with fiber access There’s a performance divide based on the type of service The CenturyLink DSL plans can range from to Mbps, which is a wide Additionally, Mbps just isn’t great these It doesn’t even reach broadband speeds (25 Mbps or more). That said, you shouldn’t have to worry about getting the advertised speed—whatever plan you sign up for, you seem to get what you pay for with On the other hand, the fiber plans offer Gigabit speeds (up to Mbps), which is Additionally, fiber internet offers synchronous download speeds and upload speeds, meaning you can game , video chat, or upload large files just as fast as you binge Fiber also tends to be inherently reliable because of the way the technology works—the light signals in fiber optic cables can carry more information over longer distances than coaxial We have no complaints about performance on these Show details Equipment and installation A fee for , but good equipment at
